						               													<description>March and Fight or Die ! are the Small War Skirmish rules for the colonial era from roughly the 1850s to the 1920s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;French Foreign Legion, the British and German Schutztruppen are all covered and so are their enemies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Without heavy weapons 2-4 players can play on a card table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Small War Games Skirmish series games are designed to be played in an area the size of a kitchen table or even a card table without heavy weapons. With more players bigger battles are possible. Each figure moves and fire in accordance with its class and the number of increments it can use per move. Firing and hand-to-hand combat rules are easy to learn. There is one combat card per set of rules that has all the tables needed to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
